CSS
css stands for cascading style-sheet.
CSS describes how html tags are to be display on screen/web browser.
CSS was introduced by Hakon Wium in 1994.
Types of CSS--------------
⦁	Internal CSS (use of Style tag)
⦁	External CSS
⦁	Inline CSS
Internal CSS-------
Syntax :---
<style>
selector{
property:value;
property:value;
property:value;property:value;property:value;
}
</style>
Selector -- Selector is used to select HTML tags to apply CSS.
Types Of  Selector :-----
1.	Tag/Element Selector
2.	Id Selector
3.	Class Selector
4.	Compound Selector
5.	Parent Child Selector
6.	nth-Child Selector
7.	first-Child Selector
8.	last-Chlid Selector
9.	nth-Child (even) Selector
10.	nth-Child (odd) Selector
11.	Attribute Selector
12.	Group Selector
13.	Universal Selector
14.	After Selector
15.	Before Selector
16.	Pseudo Selector
17.	Direct Child Selector
18.	Adjacent Siblings Selector
And Many More.........
border:width style color;--
style----
solid,dotted,double,dashed,groove,wavy and many more
text-shadow : horizontal vertical blur color;
box-shadow : horizontal vertical blur spread color side;
(spread color and side value is optional)
line-height
word-spacing
letter-spacing
Inline CSS--
<tagname style="property:value;property:value;"></tagname>
Priority of CSS----
The priority of Inline CSS is higher priority as compare to External CSS and Internal CSS.
The priority of internalCSS is higher pripority as compare to External CSS.
Transition property :--
transition: property time second,property  time in second;
transition:all time in second;
