Pattern Attribute :  to check or  verify the inputed value format we are using the pattern attribute.
Pattern uses regular expression to verify inputed value.
regular expression built by meta character and quantifires.
Meta Characters :---
[a to z] ==> allowed char --> a-z
[A to Z]==> allowed char -->A -Z
[0 -9] ==> allowed char -->0-9
[a-z,A-Z]
[a-z,A-Z,0-9]
[a-h] --> allowed char from a to h.
[A-H] --> allowed char from A to H.
[0-5] --> allowed char from 0 to 5.
[a,d,f,g] ==> a,d,f,g
[^a,d,f,g]==> excluding a,d,f,g
/d ==> digit (it will be taken all the number)
/D ==>none-digit (it will be taken all the character excluding the number)
/w ==>word[a-z,A-Z,0-9]
/W ==> none-word excluding[a-z,A-Z,0-9,_]
[@,#,$,&]
Quantifiers---
{number}
{min,max}
{min,}
{5} exactly 5 character are allowed
{2,7} minimum 2 character and maximum 7 character
{3,} minimum will be 3 and maximum character can be anything
==================================================================================Universal Selector (*)-- It will be select all the tag of the body
% -- it will taken the value of the current parent
px - it wil be fix the size 
in - it will be also taken the fix size
em-- it will be taken the just half value of the fontsize of the current parent
rem(relative em) -- it will be taken the value of the root element of html and the bydefault value of the html is 16px.
vh
vw
vmin
vmax
